estment banking capabilities.\nKey changes include 75% acquisition financing, 3:1 debt-equity ratio, and doubled finance cap to 20% of Tier 1 capital.","summary":"New M&A funding norms present $15B opportunity for banks with strong investment banking capabilities.\nKey changes include 75% acquisition financing, 3:1 debt-equity ratio, and doubled finance cap to 20% of Tier 1 capital.","url":"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/ma-funding-norms-open-up-a-15-b-opportunity-for-banks/articleshow/128532445.cms","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-19T00:00:00","source":"The Economic Times"},{"id":"502270","title":"Kotak Mahindra Bank appoints Ramesh Iyer as Independent Director for 4 years from Feb 17, 2026, succeeding Dr. Ashok Gulati.\nIyer, with over 40 years in Mahindra Group, has held key roles and won multiple industry awards like Ernst & Young Entrepreneur of the Year.","summary":"Kotak Mahindra Bank appoints Ramesh Iyer as Independent Director for 4 years from Feb 17, 2026, succeeding Dr. Ashok Gulati.\nIyer, with over 40 years in Mahindra Group, has held key roles and won multiple industry awards like Ernst & Young Entrepreneur of the Year.","url":"https://www.cnbctv18.com/business/companies/kotak-mahindra-bank-appoints-ramesh-iyer-as-independent-director-ashok-gulati-to-retire-in-march-ws-l-19852338.htm","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-17T22:48:12","source":"CNBC TV 18"},{"id":"260215154330483","title":"RBI's revised guidelines on acquisition financing enable Indian banks like SBI, Bank of India, and Kotak Mahindra Bank to participate in M&A, refinancing, and stake hikes with eased equity requirements.\nThe new norms allow unlisted firms with Rs 500 crore net worth and 3-year profitability to access financing, boosting domestic consolidation and capex in sectors like manufacturing and healthcare.","summary":"RBI's revised guidelines on acquisition financing enable Indian banks like SBI, Bank of India, and Kotak Mahindra Bank to participate 